OL,3,CMother's rare and dangerous cancer was
OL,4,Cmistaken for a verruca by doctors
OL,6,F"I thought it was probably a verruca
OL,7,Fbut I'd never had a verruca before, so
OL,8,FI went (to the pharmacy), to ask how I
OL,9,Fcould safely treat it in pregnancy.
OL,11,F"They just said they didn't think it
OL,12,Fwas a verruca, but not to worry about
OL,13,Fit if it wasn't painful and that it
OL,14,Fwould probably just go away on its
OL,15,Fown. So, I suppose I put it to the
OL,16,Fback of my mind."
